def apply(self, other):
    if isinstance(other, datetime):
        # used for detecting edge condition
        nanosecond = getattr(other, "nanosecond", 0)
        # reset timezone and nanosecond
        # other may be a Timestamp, thus not use replace
        other = datetime(
            other.year,
            other.month,
            other.day,
            other.hour,
            other.minute,
            other.second,
            other.microsecond,
        )
        n = self.n

        working_times = self.on_offset(other)

        # modification to use a fixed frequency
        idx = 0 if n >= 0 else -1
        target_time = self.start[idx]
        if working_times and other.time() in (self.start[idx], self.end[idx]):
            target_time = other.time()

        start = datetime(
            other.year, other.month, other.day,
            self.start[0].hour, 0
        )

        min_date = datetime(
            other.year, other.month, other.day,
            min([t.hour for t in self.start])
        )
		
        if start != min_date:
            target_date = start + timedelta(hours=1)
            if datetime(other.year, other.month, other.day, target_time.hour) < start:
                target_date = datetime(
                    other.year, other.month, other.day,
                    self.start[idx].hour, 0
                )
            return target_date

    else:
        raise ApplyTypeError("Only know how to combine business hour with datetime")
